-- RWE Transgas Plans to Invest $1.6 Billion in Czech Gas Network, E15 Says
-- Peter Laca
-- 2010-09-20T06:07:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-20/rwe-transgas-plans-to-invest-1-6-billion-in-czech-gas-network-e15-says.html

          
          
             RWE Transgas AS  plans to invest
about 30 billion koruna ($1.6 billion) in the Czech Republic in
the next five years to expand its natural gas infrastructure,
 E15  reported, citing Chief Executive  Martin Herrmann .  
 The investment will go mainly into expanding the
underground gas storages and building the Czech connection to
the Nord Stream gas pipeline, the newspaper said.  
